scopecontent.p:
The boxes contain 39 files and 3 scrapbooks. The files cover a variety
		  of subjects, from: appointment as Principal; financial crisis; recovery plan;
		  restructuring; graduation addresses; talks and speeches; anglicisation; new
		  University logo; and, the installation of Muriel Gray as rector. The scrapbooks
		  contain cuttings or copies of cuttings on: the closure of the Dental School;
		  the anglicisation of Edinburgh University; attacks on the University as
		  inefficient; league tables; cuttings relating to Smith personaly and generally;
		  the Chair of Scottish History; and, the sale of works of art.
